{"word":"ζωγρέω","slug":"ζωγρέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ζωγρέω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>ζωός, ἀγρεύω</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to take alive, take captive</i> instead of killing, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>(<el>ζωή, ἀγείρω</el>) <i>to restore to life, revive</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}